              <%= image_tag "behavioral-pattern.webp", alt: "Consumer’s Behavioral Pattern" %>
              <p>Regardless of how the design triggers the user experience, it is very important to understand the attributes of a design that will drive the behavioral patterns of a customer to make a decision. It is imperative for a <a href="javascript:;">UI/UX design company</a> to understand how and why a customer behaves or responds to a certain design or story. The art of understanding consumer behavior is far beyond the science of design; instead, it is a peculiar combination of psychology with sociology. On a bigger canvas, it is important for a designer to be equipped to handle it.</p>
              <h6>Visual Artistry</h6>
              <p>The aim of a <a href="javascript:;">UI/UX design agency</a> is to improve the UX by developing an understanding of the effects of illustrations, photography, typography, space, layouts, and color on the usability of products and on their aesthetic appeal. It emphasizes the aesthetics of a product and its characteristics by strategically implementing images, colors, fonts, and other elements. Successful visual artistry ensures that the soul of the page always remains the center point of focus and the engagement is driven by the design element that helps to build trust and interest in a brand. The key point to remember while mastering the art of visual artistry are</p>
              <h6>Usability</h6>
              <%= image_tag "usability.webp", alt: "Usability" %>
